<br>
It's a wild idea, however.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tim1965>Tim1965</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/21/02 1:12:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  manipulating solar flares</span><hr size=1> If you cause a star to experience an abnormal<br>
